lib-tree

0.05    2010-03-11/11:35 pm EST
        * The _get_dirs() function now returns a more complete directory list.

===========================================================================


===========================================================================
DEPENDENCIES
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Carp
Config
Cwd
File::Spec


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dependencies for Testing
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
File::Path
IO::Handle
Test::More

===========================================================================


===========================================================================
INSTALLATION
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install

Alternatively, to install with Module::Install, you can use the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

===========================================================================


===========================================================================
SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc lib::tree

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=lib-tree

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/lib-tree

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/lib-tree

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/lib-tree/

